{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AyvjZnaAoNu7iT6irdqQLa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All requirements are met. Here's a summary of what was fixed:\n\n**Root causes found and fixed:**\n\n1. **`app-user` missing `configure` on `/app`** — the permission entry existed but `configure` was set to empty string. Fixed with `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"`.\n\n2. **`ops-user` had full access on `/app`** (wrong vhost) — revoked with `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user`.\n\n3. **`ops-user` had no permissions on `/ops`** — granted full `configure/write/read` with `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"`.\n\n4. **`app-queue` pre-created with `x-queue-mode=lazy`** — the existing queue had an extra argument the `app-client` didn't expect, causing an \"inequivalent arg\" error on queue declaration. Deleted the queue; the client recreated it correctly on its next start.\n\n**Final end state:**\n- `/app`: `app-user` → `.*`/`.*`/`.*`, `ops-user` → no access\n- `/ops`: `ops-user` → `.*`/`.*`/`.*`, `app-user` → no access\n- Both `app-client` and `ops-client` are Running (0 restarts for app-client)\n- 3-node cluster healthy: `rabbitmq-0`, `rabbitmq-1`, `rabbitmq-2` all running"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":909,"cache_read_input_tokens":38929,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":909},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"71c97aa1-3134-4aab-b2b0-0cfc4906a12d","uuid":"76282b9c-3f40-460c-ac49-e8cb929f403f","request_id":"req_011Ccb1G27EgxMLiBLj5QDiZ"}
